assigned to Mills' escort

28:56.604 --> 28:59.738
says he got a call saying
there'd been a change of plan.

28:59.738 --> 29:01.652
Wolfe took his place.

29:01.652 --> 29:03.959
Nick, we need to figure out
who made that call,

29:03.959 --> 29:07.789
and why proper protocols
weren't followed.

29:07.789 --> 29:10.923
Any last-minute change
in the detail should've been
confirmed with you first.

29:12.446 --> 29:14.361
Agreed.

29:14.361 --> 29:19.366
CROWN: Okay, why would
a serial killer
take out a terrorist?

29:19.366 --> 29:22.586
He's ex-military.
Maybe he fancied
himself a hero.

29:22.586 --> 29:24.458
This guy's a hero now? No.

29:24.458 --> 29:26.808
The previous five victims
of the Fentanyl Killer

29:26.808 --> 29:30.246
all exhibited abnormal
behavior in the weeks
prior to their deaths.

29:30.246 --> 29:32.422
And?

29:32.422 --> 29:35.251
We believe he chose these
targets based on their
previous behavior shifts.

29:35.251 --> 29:37.776
You don't get more
aggressive than a terrorist
attack, that's true.

29:37.776 --> 29:41.344
CROWN:
Mills was already looking at
life imprisonment, so...

29:46.872 --> 29:51.354
So, uh, what would Rex Wolfe
gain by taking him out?
What was his...

29:51.354 --> 29:53.052
That's what
we need to figure out.

29:53.052 --> 29:54.053
Nick.

29:58.579 --> 30:00.711
Look, if you don't want
to talk right now, I get it.

30:00.711 --> 30:03.540
I just want you to know...
I could have died out there
in the woods.

30:03.540 --> 30:07.066
Rex Wolfe had a gun
to the back of my head.

30:07.066 --> 30:09.633
I was helpless.
There was nothing
I could do.

30:11.287 --> 30:14.856
I chased the biggest case
of my career.

30:17.641 --> 30:19.295
And there I was,

30:22.037 --> 30:23.430
about to die for it.

30:28.391 --> 30:29.653
All I could think about
was Flynn.

30:34.267 --> 30:36.965
What happened to him,
growing up without you.

30:42.101 --> 30:44.059
Just couldn't
let that happen again.

30:50.718 --> 30:52.154
And so, I, uh...

30:54.940 --> 30:56.158
I obeyed him.

31:16.570 --> 31:18.920
Wow. You gave me shit
for the Cheetos?

31:18.920 --> 31:21.227
You can feed
an entire nation
with that thing.

31:21.227 --> 31:25.361
So much for
dinner's grand finale.
Guess I got upstaged.

31:25.361 --> 31:27.276
You get all the Byrnes
in one room,
it's bound to happen.

31:27.276 --> 31:28.495
Just the one Byrne.

31:30.845 --> 31:33.543
I understand that everyone
wants to protect her,

31:33.543 --> 31:35.806
but we've all been
through a lot.

31:35.806 --> 31:38.722
It's just that some of us
get left eating cold,
stale pie.

31:41.160 --> 31:42.857
You been reading
my grade school diary?
[CHUCKLES]

31:45.686 --> 31:48.210
Sorry. I'm venting.

31:50.169 --> 31:53.215
Normally, I have Nick
to talk at, but I don't know.

31:55.783 --> 31:58.786
You planning on hogging
all that misery pie
for yourself?

31:58.786 --> 32:00.657
Well, you know what
misery loves.

32:13.279 --> 32:15.237
If you want me
to talk to her, I will.

32:15.237 --> 32:16.543
I don't need
someone to fix it.

32:16.543 --> 32:17.674
Okay.

32:21.852 --> 32:23.202
But it is nice to have
someone to listen.

32:27.946 --> 32:29.686
Excuse me.

32:29.686 --> 32:31.123
Byrne, good.

32:31.123 --> 32:32.951
Uh, we just had word
from the State Department

32:32.951 --> 32:33.908
that Rex Wolfe
has fled the country.

32:36.345 --> 32:39.305
Apparently, he's just crossed
into Moldova from Ukraine.

32:39.305 --> 32:42.221
Well, then his trail's
gonna go cold fast.

32:42.221 --> 32:45.659
If Rex is in Moldova,
it's only for one reason.

32:45.659 --> 32:48.749
A power vacuum is
an easy place to disappear.

32:48.749 --> 32:51.360
Governments get desperate,
they hire mercs, any mercs,

32:51.360 --> 32:55.190
